text.__SUMMARY__: Acacia sphenophylla is a shrub of the genus Acacia and the subgenus Phyllodineae. It is native to an area in the Mid West region of Western Australia.The intricate pungent shrub typically grows to a height of 0.3 to 1.3 metres (1.0 to 4.3 ft). It blooms from July to August and produces yellow flowers.
